What I would like to consider first is the concept of creating an environment, which stems from a fundamental understanding that refugees, like everyone else, are simply individuals situated in a specific context.
My colleagues at the University of Oxford and I have initiated a research project in Uganda to study the economic lives of refugees.
We chose Uganda not because it is a typical representative among host countries.
